Some 2022 film snaps. 

I made good moves in the right direction this year, and I’m thankful for that. I didn’t shoot as much personal work as I would have liked, but feels nice to look forward to more of that in 2023. 

THANKS to the people who helped me make those moves in 2022 ❤️

So happy to contribute this print to @thesongcave annual print sale, this year’s theme was BLUE. “Fire Island Doubles” is available alongside many other great photos, 5”x7” c-prints each in an edition of 75. Visit @thesongcave to purchase and support them! 💙

Pre-summer heat. NYC & Provincetown 😎

I’m excited to start sharing some of the photographs I made for THE NEW ANTIQUARIANS, a brilliant new book by @michaeldiazgriffith and published by @monacellipress . Here, the home and collection of Emily Adams Bode Aujla & Aaron Singh Aujla in NYC. 

To purchase, tap the link in my bio. 

The book features 22 brilliant young collectors from across the United States and Britain who brazenly blend the old with the new, embrace anachronism and pastiche, employ serious knowledge with humor and wit, and consider vintage and historical objects through the lens of contemporary values.
